Question: 
At Amazon, developers want to merge primary and secondary source control branches into a unified branch while preserving the order of commits from each branch. Each character of a branch represents a commit's priority, with lower alphabetical order indicating higher priority.

A conflict occurs when, in the merged branch, a commit with lower priority is placed before a commit with higher priority. Your task is to find the minimum number of conflicts in any valid merge of primary and secondary branches.

Example
primary = "zo"
secondary = "d"

There are three possible merge arrangements:

"zcdo" with 2 merge conflicts ('z' being lower priority is placed before higher priority commits 'o' and 'd')
Similarly, "zdco" with 3 merge conflicts
Similarly, "dzco" with 2 merge conflicts

The minimum number of merge conflicts possible is 2.

Function Description

Complete the function getMinimumConflicts that takes the following input:

string primary: the commit sequence of the primary branch
string secondary: the commit sequence of the secondary branch
Returns
int: the minimum number of conflicts after a valid merge
Constraints
1 ≤ |primary|, |secondary| ≤ 1000
primary and secondary consist of lowercase English letters only.
Input Format for Custom Testing

(Standard HackerRank custom input format.)

Sample Case 0
Sample Input 0
STDIN      FUNCTION
-----      --------
dae   ->   primary = "dae"
add   ->   secondary = "add"
Sample Output 0
1

Solution:
import java.util.*;

class Main {
    
    public static int getInversionCost(int idx,String s,char last_ch) {

        int count=0;
        for(int i=idx;i<s.length();i++) {
            if(last_ch>s.charAt(i)) {
                count++;
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
   
    public static int getMinConflitMerge(int idx1,int idx2,String s,String t,int[][] dp) {
        if(idx1>=s.length() && idx2>=t.length()) return 0;

        if(idx1>=s.length() && idx2<t.length()) {
            char ch = t.charAt(idx2);
            int cur_cost = getInversionCost(idx2+1,t,ch);
            return cur_cost+getMinConflitMerge(idx1,idx2+1,s,t,dp);
        }

        if(idx2>=t.length() && idx1<s.length()) {
            char ch = s.charAt(idx1);
            int cur_cost = getInversionCost(idx1+1,s,ch);
            return cur_cost+getMinConflitMerge(idx1+1,idx2,s,t,dp);
        }

        if(dp[idx1][idx2]!=-1) return dp[idx1][idx2];

       //choosing s
        char ch = s.charAt(idx1);
        int choose_s = getInversionCost(idx1+1,s,ch) +getInversionCost(idx2,t,ch)+ getMinConflitMerge(idx1+1,idx2,s,t,dp);

        //choosing t
        char cr = t.charAt(idx2);
        int choose_t = getInversionCost(idx2+1,t,cr) + getInversionCost(idx1,s,cr)+ getMinConflitMerge(idx1,idx2+1,s,t,dp);

        return dp[idx1][idx2] = Math.min(choose_s,choose_t);
    }

    public static int minConflitMerge(String s,String t) {
        int[][] dp = new int[s.length()+1][t.length()+1];
        for(int[] d : dp) {
            Arrays.fill(d,-1);
        }

        return getMinConflitMerge(0,0,s,t,dp);
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        String s = sc.next();
        String t = sc.next();

        System.out.println(minConflitMerge(s,t));
    }
}  
